	Fractional increase in diabetes deaths if full distancing*Social distancing affecting chronic disease deaths
	~	dmnl [0,1,0.05]
	~		|

Fractional increase in diabetes deaths if full distancing=
	0.1
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Fractional increase in family homicides=
	Fractional increase in family homicides if full distancing*Social distancing affecting deaths of despair
	~	dmnl [0,1,0.05]
	~		|

Fractional increase in family homicides if full distancing=
	0.2
	~	dmnl [0,1,0.05]
	~		|

Fractional increase in other acute infect deaths=
	Fractional increase in other acute infect deaths if full distancing*Social distancing affecting acute disease deaths
	~	dmnl [0,1,0.05]
	~		|

Fractional increase in other acute infect deaths if full distancing=
	0.1
	~	dmnl [0,1,0.05]
	~	flu, pneumonia, UTI, food poisoning, STD
	|

Fractional increase in suicides=
	Fractional increase in suicides if full distancing*Social distancing affecting deaths of despair
	~	dmnl [0,1,0.05]
	~		|

Fractional increase in suicides if full distancing=
	0.2
	~	dmnl [0,1,0.05]
	~		|

GDP billions per yr reference=
	Total popn reference * GDP per capita per yr reference / Dollars per billion dollars
	~	bdollars/year
	~		|

GDP loss billions=
	GDP billions per yr reference * GDP loss fraction / Months per year
	~	bdollars/Month
	~		|

GDP loss fraction=
	GDP loss fraction if full distancing*Social distancing
	~	dmnl
	~		|

GDP loss fraction if full distancing=
	0.15
	~	dmnl [0,0.5,0.05]
	~	See: \
		https://www.mckinsey.com/business-functions/strategy-and-corporate-finance/\
		our-insights/safeguarding-our-lives-and-our-livelihoods-the-imperative-of-o\
		ur-time.  McKinsey estimates 13% loss by 2020Q3 in their "muted recovery" \
		scenario.
	|

GDP per capita per yr reference=
	67000
	~	dollars/popn/year
	~		|

Hospital admissions=
	Becoming symptomatic * Severe frac of infected sympto * Hospitalized frac of severe
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Hospitalized=
	Severe * Hospitalized frac of severe
	~	popn
	~		|

Hospitalized frac of cumul cases=
	MIN(1,ZIDZ(Cumul hospitalized,Cumul reported cases))
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Hospitalized frac of severe=
	Lookup for hospitalized frac of severe(Severe ratio to critical care cap/Tolerable severe ratio to critical care cap\
		)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Ideal critical care cap=
	Severe/Tolerable severe ratio to critical care cap
	~	popn
	~		|

Impending reported new cases=
	Becoming symptomatic*Tested frac of sympto + New infections*Tested frac of presympto
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Incoming infections=
	Effect of vaccine on infection probability * IF THEN ELSE(Time<=Date of first incoming infections\
		,0, IF THEN ELSE(Time<=Date of peak incoming infections
	, Incoming infections at peak
	*(Time-Date of first incoming infections)/(Date of peak incoming infections-Date of first incoming infections\
		), IF THEN ELSE
	(Time<=Date of final prevaccine incoming infections, Incoming infections at peak - (\
		Incoming infections at peak-Incoming infections final prevaccine
	)*(Time-Date of peak incoming infections)/(Date of final prevaccine incoming infections\
		-Date of peak incoming infections
	), Incoming infections final prevaccine
	)))
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Incoming infections at peak=
	300
	~	popn/Month [0,400,25]
	~		|

Incoming infections final prevaccine=
	0
	~	popn/Month [0,400,25]
	~		|

Increase in deaths of despair=
	(Deaths of despair per day-Deaths of despair per day normal)*Days per month
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Increase in monthly alcohol OD deaths=
	Alcohol OD deaths per year normal/Months per year * Fractional increase in alcohol OD deaths
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Increase in monthly chronic respir disease deaths=
	Chronic respir disease deaths per year normal/Months per year * Fractional increase in chronic respir disease deaths
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Increase in monthly CVD and hypertn deaths=
	CVD and hypertn deaths per year normal/Months per year * Fractional increase in CVD and hypertn deaths
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Increase in monthly diabetes deaths=
	Diabetes deaths per year normal/Months per year * Fractional increase in diabetes deaths
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Increase in monthly drug OD deaths=
	Accidental drug OD deaths per year normal/Months per year * Fractional increase in accidental drug OD deaths
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Increase in monthly family homicides=
	Family homicides per year normal/Months per year * Fractional increase in family homicides
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Increase in monthly suicides=
	Suicides per year normal/Months per year * Fractional increase in suicides
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Increase in other acute infect deaths=
	Other acute infect deaths per year normal/Months per year * Fractional increase in other acute infect deaths
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Increase in other disease deaths=
	Specified other disease deaths per day-Specified other disease deaths per day normal
	~	popn/day
	~		|

Incubation period=
	0.18
	~	months [0,0.5,0.01]
	~	.18 month = 5.4 days
	|

Infected=
	Infected presympto + Infected sympto
	~	popn
	~		|

Infected presympto= INTEG (
	New infections-Becoming symptomatic,
		0)
	~	popn
	~		|

Infected sympto= INTEG (
	Becoming symptomatic-Fatalities-Recoveries,
		0)
	~	popn
	~		|

Infection probability per contact=
	Infection probability per contact initial * Effect of vaccine on infection probability\
		 * Effect of season on transmission
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Infection probability per contact initial=
	0.011
	~	dmnl [0,0.02,0.001]
	~	(v1: .22, v2: .22; v2c: .105; v2e: .11; v3: .115; v4b: .112; v5: .113)  \
		But see: \
		https://www.uptodate.com/contents/coronavirus-disease-2019-covid-19-epidemi\
		ology-virology-clinical-features-diagnosis-and-prevention#H3174740477.  US \
		0.45%, S Korea 0.55%, China 5%
	|

Infectious contacts=
	Infected sympto*Contacts per sympto + Infected presympto*Reltv infectiousness of presymptos\
		*Contacts per presympto
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Infectious contacts with susceptible=
	Infectious contacts * Susceptible fraction of popn
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Input series for tested frac of mild and mod sympto(
	[(1,0)-(4.5,1)],(1,0.04),(1.25,0.04),(1.5,0.09),(1.75,0.25),(2,0.4),(2.25,0.5),(2.5,\
		0.5),(2.75,0.5),(3,0.36),(3.25,0.26),(3.5,0.48),(3.75,0.58),(4,0.58),(4.25,0.58),(4.5\
		,0.58))
	~	dmnl
	~	V7: \
		(1,0.04),(1.25,0.04),(1.5,0.09),(1.75,0.15),(2,0.22),(2.25,0.265),(2.5,0.36\
		),(2.75,0.39),(3,0.36),(3.25,0.26),(3.5,0.48),(3.75,0.58),(4,0.58),(4.25,0.\
		58),(4.5,0.58)
	|

Isolation fatigue=
	Lookup for isolation fatigue(Recent distancing affecting isolation fatigue)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Lookup for effect of season on transmission(
	[(0,0.9)-(12,1)],(0,1),(1,1),(2,1),(3,1),(4,1),(5,1),(6,1),(7,1),(8,1),(9,1),(10,1),\
		(11,1),(12,1))
	~	dmnl
	~	Luo et al MedRxiv 2-12-20 tentatively concludes higher humidity enhances \
		transmission while higher temperature impedes it.  Possible then that \
		summer will improve the situation in arid areas but not in humid ones.
	|

Lookup for hospitalized frac of severe(
	[(0,0)-(24,1)],(0,1),(1,1),(2,0.9),(4,0.75),(6,0.6),(8,0.45),(10,0.35),(12,0.28),(16\
		,0.2),(20,0.15),(24,0.13))
	~	dmnl
	~	In high load conditions, some severe cases don't get hospitalized due to \
		shortages of one or more types of critical care assets: personnel, \
		materials, equipment (aside from ventilators, handled separately here), \
		vehicles.
	|

Lookup for isolation fatigue(
	[(0,0)-(1,1)],(0,0),(0.1,0),(0.2,0.04),(0.3,0.1),(0.4,0.16),(0.5,0.25),(0.6,0.35),(0.7\
		,0.48),(0.8,0.63),(0.9,0.8),(1,1))
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Lookup for mobility reduction(
	[(0,0)-(0.5,1)],(0,0),(0.05,0.22),(0.1,0.32),(0.15,0.36),(0.2,0.39),(0.25,0.41),(0.3\
		,0.42),(0.35,0.43),(0.4,0.44),(0.45,0.45),(0.5,0.45))
	~	dmnl
	~	People will first eliminate their discretionary travel and after that \
		their social interactions.  (It would take a complete quarantine, \
		something not modeled here, for them to cut their non-discretionary travel \
		for food and supplies.)  Thus, mobility reduction should rise faster than \
		social distancing at first, but will hit a maximum representing the \
		discretionary fraction of travel miles.
	|

Lookup for social distancing(
	[(0,0)-(3,1)],(0,0),(0.5,0.27),(1,0.5),(1.5,0.67),(2,0.8),(2.5,0.84),(3,0.84))
	~	dmnl
	~	through v5: \
		(0,0),(0.5,0.27),(1,0.5),(1.5,0.67),(2,0.8),(2.5,0.9),(3,0.95); v6: \
		(0,0),(0.5,0.27),(1,0.5),(1.5,0.67),(2,0.8),(2.5,0.88),(3,0.9); v6: up to \
		0.85
	|

Lost life value billions=
	YLL net change from all outcomes * Valuation of year of life lost / Dollars per billion dollars
	~	bdollars/Month
	~		|

Lost resolve from isolation fatigue=
	Isolation fatigue*Max lost resolve from isolation fatigue
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Max critical care capacity=
	Critical care capacity initial*Multiple for max critical care cap
	~	popn [100000,600000,50000]
	~		|

Max lost resolve from isolation fatigue=
	0.25
	~	dmnl [0,1,0.05]
	~		|

Mobility reduction=
	Lookup for mobility reduction(Social distancing)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Months elapsed in year=
	MODULO(Time,12)
	~	Month
	~	0 = Jan 1st; 11.97 = Dec 31st.
	|

Months per year=
	12
	~	months/year
	~		|

Multiple for max critical care cap=
	4
	~	dmnl [1,6,0.5]
	~		|

New infections=
	Incoming infections + New infections domestic
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

New infections domestic=
	Infectious contacts with susceptible * Infection probability per contact
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Nonfamily homicide deaths per day=
	Nonfamily homicides per year normal*(1-Fractional decrease in nonfamily homicide deaths\
		)/Days per year
	~	popn/day
	~	See "Deaths by age group" spreadsheet; 2018 data from WONDER.
	|

Nonfamily homicide deaths per million normal=
	50.7
	~	1/year
	~	See "Deaths by age group" spreadsheet; 2018 data from WONDER.
	|

Nonfamily homicides per year normal=
	Total popn reference/1e+06*Nonfamily homicide deaths per million normal
	~	popn/year
	~	See "Deaths by age group" spreadsheet; 2018 data on total homicides from \
		WONDER (18830), less 2017 family homicides from NY Times (2237).
	|

Other acute infect deaths per day=
	Other acute infect deaths per year normal*(1+Fractional increase in other acute infect deaths\
		)/Days per year
	~	popn/day
	~	See "Deaths by age group" spreadsheet; 2018 data from WONDER.
	|

Other acute infect deaths per million normal=
	390.2
	~	1/year
	~	See "Deaths by age group" spreadsheet; 2018 data from WONDER.
	|

Other acute infect deaths per year normal=
	Total popn reference/1e+06*Other acute infect deaths per million normal
	~	popn/year
	~	See "Deaths by age group" spreadsheet; 2018 data from WONDER.
	|

Past infections=
	Dead from COVID+Recovered
	~	popn
	~		|

Potential cases per million contact traced per day=
	0
	~	1/day [0,60,1]
	~	max traceable new cases per day per million popn
	|

Potential for catch up reporting of dead=
	Dead from COVID*MAX(0,Reported frac of fatalities-Reported frac of dead)
	~	popn
	~		|

Presympto frac of infected=
	XIDZ(Infected presympto, Infected, 1)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Recent distancing affecting isolation fatigue=
	SMOOTHI(Social distancing,Time to develop isolation fatigue,0)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Recent fatalities per day affecting social distancing=
	SMOOTH3I(COVID fatalities per day,Time to adjust social distancing,0)
	~	popn/day
	~		|

Recent fatalities per day for 50pct social distancing=
	Total popn reference/1e+06*Recent fatalities per million per day for 50pct distancing
	~	popn/day [100,300,10]
	~	v2d: 200k confirmed cases; v3: 150k confirmed cases; v4: 1700 deaths in 2 \
		weeks; v4a: 2000 deaths in 2 wks; v4b: 133 deaths per day avg past 2 \
		weeks; v5a: 133; v5b: 115; v5c: 140; v5d: 150; v6c:165
	|

Recent fatalities per million per day for 50pct distancing=
	0.606
	~	1/day [0.4,0.8,0.01]
	~	.606 per million*330m = 200 per day
	|

Recovered= INTEG (
	Recoveries,
		0)
	~	popn
	~		|

Recoveries=
	Infected sympto*(1-Fatal frac of sympto)/Avg time to death or recovery
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Reltv contacts per sympto=
	0.5
	~	dmnl [0,1,0.05]
	~	This is the combination of behaviors for severe, moderate, and mild.  The \
		model assumes the relative proportions of the three types remain constant.  \
		If it's 18% severe (and.05 still socialize), 25% mild (.95 still \
		socialize) and 57% moderate (.43 still socialize), then weighted average \
		is 0.5 socializing relative to an asymptomatic.
	|

Reltv infectiousness of presymptos=
	0.5
	~	dmnl [0,100,5]
	~	v1: 0.2; v3: 0.5
	|

Reported dead= INTEG (
	Reported fatalities,
		0)
	~	popn
	~		|

Reported dead frac of cases=
	ZIDZ(Reported dead, Cumul reported cases)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Reported fatalities=
	Fatalities*Reported frac of fatalities + Catch up reporting of past fatalities per day\
		*Days per month
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Reported fatalities per day=
	Reported fatalities/Days per month
	~	popn/day
	~		|

Reported fatalities ratio to new cases=
	ZIDZ(Reported fatalities per day,Reported new cases per day)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Reported frac of cumulative infections=
	ZIDZ(Cumul reported cases, Infected+Past infections)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Reported frac of dead=
	XIDZ(Reported dead, Dead from COVID, Reported frac of fatalities)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Reported frac of fatalities=
	IF THEN ELSE(Time<Date to change reporting of fatalities, Reported frac of fatalities initial\
		, Reported frac of fatalities including probables)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Reported frac of fatalities including probables=
	1
	~	dmnl [0.6,1,0.01]
	~		|

Reported frac of fatalities initial=
	0.89
	~	dmnl [0.6,1,0.01]
	~	Through v7: 0.7
	|

Reported frac of fatalities to include probables=
	MAX(0, Reported frac of fatalities - Reported frac of fatalities initial)
	~	dmnl
	~	Increase reflects April 14 change in NYC reporting to include probables: \
		https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/us-data/.
	|

Reported new cases=
	SMOOTHI(Impending reported new cases, Time to get tested,0) + Reported probable fatalities per day\
		*Days per month
	~	popn/Month
	~		|

Reported new cases per day=
	Reported new cases/Days per month
	~	popn/day
	~		|

Reported probable fatalities per day=
	Catch up reporting of past fatalities per day + (Fatalities*Reported frac of fatalities to include probables\
		/Days per month)
	~	popn/day
	~		|

Severe=
	Infected sympto * Severe frac of infected sympto
	~	popn
	~		|

Severe frac of infected sympto=
	0.08
	~	dmnl [0,0.3,0.005]
	~	V2a: 0.14; v2b: .155; v2c: .16; v2d: .14; v2e: .15; v3: .14; v6: 0.18; v7: \
		0.175
	|

Severe ratio to critical care cap=
	Severe/Critical care capacity
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Social distancing=
	Social distancing if no fatigue * (1-Lost resolve from isolation fatigue)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Social distancing affecting acute disease deaths=
	SMOOTH(Social distancing, Time for distancing to impact other acute infections)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Social distancing affecting chronic disease deaths=
	SMOOTH(Social distancing, Time for distancing to impact chronic disease)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Social distancing affecting deaths of despair=
	SMOOTH(Social distancing, Time for distancing to impact deaths of despair)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Social distancing if no fatigue=
	Lookup for social distancing(Recent fatalities per day affecting social distancing/Recent fatalities per day for 50pct social distancing
	)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Specified other disease deaths per day=
	CVD and hypertn deaths per day+Diabetes deaths per day+Chronic respir disease deaths per day\
		+Other acute infect deaths per day
	~	popn/day
	~		|

Specified other disease deaths per day normal= INITIAL(
	Specified other disease deaths per day)
	~	popn/day
	~		|

Street deaths per day=
	Vehicle accident deaths per day+Nonfamily homicide deaths per day
	~	popn/day
	~		|

Street deaths per day normal= INITIAL(
	Street deaths per day)
	~	popn/day
	~		|

Suicides per day=
	Suicides per year normal*(1+Fractional increase in suicides)/Days per year
	~	popn/day
	~	See "Deaths by age group" spreadsheet; 2018 data from WONDER.
	|

Suicides per million normal=
	147.8
	~	1/year
	~	See "Deaths by age group" spreadsheet; 2018 data from WONDER.
	|

Suicides per year normal=
	Total popn reference/1e+06*Suicides per million normal
	~	popn/year
	~	See "Deaths by age group" spreadsheet; 2018 data from WONDER.
	|

Susceptible= INTEG (
	-New infections,
		Total popn reference)
	~	popn
	~		|

Susceptible fraction of popn=
	Susceptible/Total popn
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Tested frac of mild and mod sympto=
	Input series for tested frac of mild and mod sympto(Time)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Tested frac of presympto=
	0.04
	~	dmnl [0,0.4,0.01]
	~	Testing based on at-risk status; e.g. some elderly in nursing homes or \
		group residences.
	|

Tested frac of severe sympto=
	0.95
	~	dmnl [0.8,1,0.01]
	~		|

Tested frac of sympto=
	Tested frac of severe sympto*Severe frac of infected sympto
	 + Tested frac of mild and mod sympto*(1-Severe frac of infected sympto)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Time for distancing to impact chronic disease=
	3
	~	Month
	~		|

Time for distancing to impact deaths of despair=
	1
	~	Month [0.25,2,0.25]
	~		|

Time for distancing to impact other acute infections=
	0.5
	~	Month
	~		|

Time of vaccine availability=
	15
	~	Month [0,24,1]
	~		|

Time to adjust critical care cap=
	2
	~	months [0.5,6,0.25]
	~	through v6: 2
	|

Time to adjust social distancing=
	0.5
	~	months [0,2,0.25]
	~		|

Time to develop isolation fatigue=
	1
	~	months [0.25,2,0.25]
	~		|

Time to get tested=
	0.17
	~	months [0.05,0.35,0.01]
	~	.17 month = 5 days
	|

Time to trace and quarantine=
	0.25
	~	Month [0,10000,1000]
	~		|

Tolerable severe ratio to critical care cap=
	0.125
	~	dmnl [0,0.5,0.05]
	~	Through v7: 0.25; Reflects highly uneven geographical distribution of \
		critical care resources per capita. Large urban hospitals generally have \
		higher utilization, thus less spare capacity for disaster response, than \
		smaller hospitals.
	|

Total popn=
	Total popn reference - Dead from COVID
	~	popn
	~		|

Total popn reference=
	3.3e+08
	~	popn
	~		|

Vaccine effectiveness and reach=
	0.2
	~	dmnl [0,1,0.05]
	~		|

Valuation of year of life lost=
	100000
	~	dollars/popn/year
	~		|

Vehicle accident deaths per day=
	Vehicle accident deaths per year normal*(1-Fractional decrease in vehicle accident deaths\
		)/Days per year
	~	popn/day
	~	See "Deaths by age group" spreadsheet; 2018 data from WONDER.
	|

Vehicle accident deaths per million normal=
	126.2
	~	1/year
	~	See "Deaths by age group" spreadsheet; 2018 data from WONDER.
	|

Vehicle accident deaths per year normal=
	Total popn reference/1e+06*Vehicle accident deaths per million normal
	~	popn/year
	~	See "Deaths by age group" spreadsheet; 2018 data from WONDER.
	|

YLG from fewer nonfamily homicides=
	Decrease in monthly nonfamily homicides * Avg YLL per nonfamily homicide
	~	popn*years/Month
	~		|

YLG from fewer street deaths=
	YLG from fewer nonfamily homicides + YLG from fewer vehicle accident deaths
	~	popn*years/Month
	~	Years of life gained
	|

YLG from fewer vehicle accident deaths=
	Decrease in monthly vehicle accident deaths * Avg YLL per vehicle accident death
	~	popn*years/Month
	~		|

YLL from adverse nonCovid outcomes=
	YLL from increased deaths of despair + YLL from increased other disease deaths
	~	popn*years/Month
	~	Years of life lost
	|

YLL from Covid fatalities=
	Fatalities * Avg YLL per Covid fatality
	~	popn*years/Month
	~		|

YLL from increased alcohol OD deaths=
	Increase in monthly alcohol OD deaths * Avg YLL per alcohol OD death
	~	popn*years/Month
	~		|

YLL from increased chronic respir disease deaths=
	Increase in monthly chronic respir disease deaths * Avg YLL per chronic respir disease death
	~	popn*years/Month
	~		|

YLL from increased CVD and hypertn deaths=
	Increase in monthly CVD and hypertn deaths * Avg YLL per CVD and hypertn death
	~	popn*years/Month
	~		|

YLL from increased deaths of despair=
	YLL from increased suicides + YLL from increased family homicides + YLL from increased drug OD deaths\
		 + YLL from increased alcohol OD deaths
	~	popn*years/Month
	~		|

YLL from increased diabetes deaths=
	Increase in monthly diabetes deaths * Avg YLL per diabetes death
	~	popn*years/Month
	~		|

YLL from increased drug OD deaths=
	Increase in monthly drug OD deaths * Avg YLL per accidental drug overdose death
	~	popn*years/Month
	~		|

YLL from increased family homicides=
	Increase in monthly family homicides * Avg YLL per family homicide
	~	popn*years/Month
	~		|

YLL from increased other acute infect deaths=
	Increase in other acute infect deaths * Avg YLL per other acute infect death
	~	popn*years/Month
	~		|

YLL from increased other disease deaths=
	YLL from increased chronic respir disease deaths + YLL from increased diabetes deaths\
		 + YLL from increased CVD and hypertn deaths + YLL from increased other acute infect deaths
	~	popn*years/Month
	~		|

YLL from increased suicides=
	Increase in monthly suicides * Avg YLL per suicide
	~	popn*years/Month
	~		|

YLL net change from all outcomes=
	YLL from Covid fatalities + YLL net change from nonCovid outcomes
	~	popn*years/Month
	~		|

YLL net change from nonCovid outcomes=
	YLL from adverse nonCovid outcomes - YLG from fewer street deaths
	~	popn*years/Month
	~	Years of life lost
	|

********************************************************
	.Control
********************************************************~
		Simulation Control Parameters
	|

Combined loss billions=
	GDP loss billions + Lost life value billions
	~	bdollars/Month
	~		|

FINAL TIME  = 24
	~	Month
	~	The final time for the simulation.
	|

INITIAL TIME  = 0
	~	Month
	~	The initial time for the simulation.
	|

SAVEPER  = 
        TIME STEP
	~	Month [0,?]
	~	The frequency with which output is stored.
	|

TIME STEP  = 0.03125
	~	Month [0,?]
	~	The time step for the simulation.
	|

********************************************************
	.Hist
********************************************************~
		Historical data
	|

Cumul reported cases data:RAW::=
	GET XLS DATA('Covid19US data.xlsx','Data','c','d5')
	~	popn
	~		|

Mobility reduction data:RAW::=
	GET XLS DATA('Covid19US data.xlsx','Data','c','f5')
	~	popn
	~	Source for mobility decrease: \
		https://www.unacast.com/covid19/social-distancing-scoreboard
	|

Reported dead data:RAW::=
	GET XLS DATA('Covid19US data.xlsx','Data','c','e5')
	~	popn
	~		|

Reported dead frac of cases data:RAW::=
	X IF MISSING(Reported dead data/Cumul reported cases data,:NA:)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Reported fatalities per day data:RAW::=
	GET XLS DATA('Covid19US data.xlsx','Data','c','i5')
	~	popn/day
	~		|

Reported fatalities ratio to new cases data:RAW::=
	X IF MISSING(ZIDZ(Reported fatalities per day data,Reported new cases per day data),\
		:NA:)
	~	dmnl
	~		|

Reported new cases per day data:RAW::=
	GET XLS DATA('Covid19US data.xlsx','Data','c','h5')
	~	popn/day
	~		|

********************************************************
	.Stats
********************************************************~
		Summary Statistics
	|

Residuals reported fatalities per day = SSTATS(Reported fatalities per day data,Reported fatalities per day\
		:R2 Reported fatalities per day,MAE Reported fatalities per day,MAEM Reported fatalities per day\
		,MAPE Reported fatalities per day,RMSE Reported fatalities per day,MSE Reported fatalities per day\
		,Um Reported fatalities per day,Us Reported fatalities per day,Uc Reported fatalities per day\
		,Count Reported fatalities per day)
	~	popn/day
	~		|

Residuals reported new cases per day = SSTATS(Reported new cases per day data,Reported new cases per day\
